UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1986
1 A RESOLUTION adjourning the Senate in honor and loving memory of Jack
2 Conley Morgan.
3 WHEREAS, Jack Conley Morgan was born on July 20, 1951, in Hoskinston,
4 Kentucky, the son of the late Sam and Ethel Morgan; and
5 WHEREAS, Jack Conley Morgan lived a life characterized by a strong work ethic
6 and commitment to his family and friends. Jack had a penchant for industry and hard
7 work, serving as owner and operator of Mountain Logging and J & C Service Station,
8 and as a former coal mine owner and operator; and
9 WHEREAS, Jack Conley Morgan had a restless desire to better himself and his
10 world, which extended to his own education. After graduating from Leslie County High
11 School, Jack attended Cumberland College in Williamsburg, Kentucky. Benefiting from
12 the rewards of education, Jack would spend the rest of his life advocating the importance
13 of education; and
14 WHEREAS, Jack Conley Morgan had endless compassion and desire to help others
15 which was exemplified by his founding and daily operation of the "Hope in the Hills"
16 organization that provided free food to thousands of his fellow Leslie County residents,
17 especially children. Jack never stopped giving back to the community that made him; and
18 WHEREAS, Jack Conley Morgan loved his family and enjoyed spending time with
19 his children and grandchildren, hunting and four-wheeling. His legacy will continue
20 through his family; and
21 WHEREAS, Jack Conley Morgan departed this earthly life on December 19, 2025.
22 He is survived by the mother of his children, Sandra Duff Morgan; his two loving
23 daughters, Jackie Morgan (Jeff) Johnson and Andrea (Tate) Begley; his two sisters, Judy
24 Rose Saylor and Carmolitta (Johnny) Pace; and his five grandchildren, Jared Johnson,
25 Josh Johnson, Jaelyn Johnson, Tatum Begley, and Will Begley. Jack was preceded in
26 death by his parents, Sam and Ethel Morgan; his sister Carolene (Herman) Coy; his
27 brother, J.B. (Shirley) Morgan; and his brother-in-law, James Saylor;
